label: accountant
gloss: An office for an accountant.

label: advertising agency
gloss: A service-based business dedicated to creating, planning, and handling advertising.

label: architect
gloss: An office for an architect or group of architects.

label: association
gloss: An office of a non-profit organisation, society, e.g. student, sport, consumer, automobile, bike association, etc.

label: charity
gloss: An office of a charitable organization

label: company
gloss: An office of a private company

label: consulting
gloss: An office for a consulting firm, providing expert professional advice to other companies or organisations.

label: courier
gloss: A courier company

label: coworking
gloss: An office where people can go to work (might require a fee); not limited to a single employer

label: educational institution
gloss: An office for an educational institution.

label: employment agency
gloss: An office for an employment service.

label: energy supplier
gloss: An office for a energy supplier.

label: engineer
gloss: An office for an engineer or group of engineers.

label: estate agent
gloss: A place where you can rent or buy a house.

label: financial
gloss: An office of a company in the financial sector

label: financial advisor
gloss: A professional who offers financial planning and sells financial services to clients.

label: forestry
gloss: A forestry office

label: foundation
gloss: An office of a foundation

label: government
gloss: An office of a (supra)national, regional or local government agency or department

label: graphic design
gloss: An office of a graphic designer

label: guide
gloss: An office for tour guides, mountain guides, dive guides, etc.

label: harbour master
gloss: The Harbour-master's office

label: insurance
gloss: An office at which you can take out insurance policies.

label: it office
gloss: An office for an IT specialist.

label: lawyer
gloss: An office for a lawyer.

label: logistics
gloss: An office for a forwarder / hauler.

label: moving company
gloss: An office which offers a relocation service.

label: newspaper
gloss: An office of a newspaper

label: ngo
gloss: An office for a non-profit, non-governmental organisation (NGO).

label: notary
gloss: An office for a notary public (common law)

label: political party
gloss: An office of a political party

label: property management
gloss: Office of a company, which manages a real estate property.

label: quango
gloss: An office of a quasi-autonomous non-governmental organisation.

label: religion
gloss: office of a community of faith

label: research
gloss: An office for research and development

label: surveyor
gloss: An office of a person doing technical surveys, such as land surveys or risk and damage evaluations of properties and equipment.

label: tax advisor
gloss: An office for a financial expert specially trained in tax law

label: telecommunication
gloss: An office for a telecommunication company

label: water utility
gloss: The office for a water utility company or water board.

label: adult gaming centre
gloss: A venue with gambling machines and other pay-to-play games.

label: amusement arcade
gloss: A venue with pay-to-play games, such as video games, driving simulators, pinball machines, merchandisers, etc.

label: bandstand
gloss: An open structure where musical bands can perform concerts.

label: beach resort
gloss: To mark the boundary of a managed beach.

label: bird hide
gloss: A place to observe birds.

label: bleachers
gloss: Raised, tiered rows of benches found at spectator events

label: bowling alley
gloss: A facility that is equipped to play the game of bowling.

label: common
gloss: A common land (deprecated).

label: dance
gloss: A place to go dancing.

label: disc golf course
gloss: Disc golf course

label: dog park
gloss: Designated area, with or without a fenced boundary, where dog-owners are permitted to exercise their pets unrestrained.

label: escape game
gloss: A physical adventure game in which players solve a series of puzzles using clues, hints and strategy to complete the objectives at hand.

label: firepit
gloss: A permanent location or structure to host campfires, bonfires, etc.

label: fishing
gloss: A place for fishing.

label: fitness centre
gloss: A place with exercise machines and/or fitness/dance classes.

label: fitness station
gloss: A place with exercise machines, single or collection of, outdoor.

label: garden
gloss: Place where flowers and other plants are grown in a decorative and structured manner or for scientific purposes.

label: golf course
gloss: A golf course.

label: hackerspace
gloss: A place where people with common interests, often in computers, technology, science, digital art or electronic art, can meet, socialize and/or collaborate.

label: horse riding
gloss: A facility where people practise horse riding, usually in their spare time, e.g. a riding centre.

label: ice rink
gloss: A place where you can skate or play ice hockey.

label: marina
gloss: For mooring leisure yachts and motor boats.

label: miniature golf
gloss: A place or area that you can play miniature golf.

label: nature reserve
gloss: Protected area of importance for wildlife, flora, fauna or features of geological or other special interest.

label: outdoor seating
gloss: Areas for outdoor gastronomy.

label: park
gloss: Open, green area for recreation, usually municipal.

label: picnic table
gloss: A picnic table

label: pitch
gloss: A field for playing football, soccer, cricket, baseball, tennis, etc., a riding arena or a skate park.

label: playground
gloss: Playground for little children.

label: resort
gloss: A place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for vacations, tourism and/or going swimming in a pool and/or a nearby body of water.

label: sauna
gloss: A small room or house designed to experience dry or wet heat sessions, or an establishment with one or more of these and auxiliary facilities.

label: slipway
gloss: Boats can be launched here.

label: sports centre
gloss: A distinct facility where a range of sports take place within an enclosed area.

label: sports hall
gloss: A building that is used as a sports hall.

label: stadium
gloss: A major sports arena with substantial tiered seating.

label: swimming area
gloss: A swimming area - place over river, lake or other water reservoir where swimming is allowed.

label: swimming pool
gloss: A swimming pool (water area only).

label: tanning salon
gloss: Place where customers can use UV lamps to tan their skin.

label: track
gloss: A track for running, cycling and other non-motorised racing such as horses, greyhounds.

label: water park
gloss: An amusement park with features like water slides, recreational pools (e.g. wave pools) or lazy rivers.

label: wildlife hide
gloss: A place to observe wildlife.

label: quarter
gloss: A quarter is a named, geographically localised place within a suburb of a larger city or within a town which is bigger than a neighbourhood

label: neighbourhood
gloss: A neighbourhood is a smaller named, geographically localised place within a suburb of a larger city or within a town or village

label: city block
gloss: A named city block, usually surrounded by streets.

label: plot
gloss: A named plot is a tract or parcel of land owned or meant to be owned by some owner.

label: town
gloss: An important urban centre, between a village and a city in size.

label: village
gloss: A smaller distinct settlement, smaller than a town with few facilities available with people traveling to nearby towns to access these.

label: hamlet
gloss: A smaller rural community, typically with fewer than 100-200 inhabitants, and little infrastructure.

label: isolated dwelling
gloss: The smallest kind of settlement (1-2 households).

label: farm
gloss: An individually named farm.

label: allotments
gloss: A separate settlement, which is located outside an officially inhabited locality and has its own addressing

label: archipelago
gloss: A named group or chain of closely related islands and islets.

label: island
gloss: Any piece of land that is completely surrounded by water and isolated from other significant landmasses.

label: islet
gloss: A very small island.

label: square
gloss: A town or village square: a paved open public space, generally of architectural significance, which is surrounded by buildings in a built-up area such as a city, town or village.

label: locality
gloss: A named place that has no population.

label: apartments
gloss: A building arranged into individual dwellings, often on separate floors. May also have retail outlets on the ground floor.

label: bungalow
gloss: A single-storey detached small house, Dacha.

label: cabin
gloss: A cabin is a small, roughly built house usually with a wood exterior and typically found in rural areas.

label: detached
gloss: A detached house, a free-standing residential building usually housing a single family.

label: dormitory
gloss: A shared building intended for college/university students (not a share room for multiple occupants as implied by the term in British English).

label: farm
gloss: A residential building on a farm (farmhouse).

label: ger
gloss: A permanent or seasonal round yurt or ger used as dwelling.

label: hotel
gloss: A building designed with separate rooms available for overnight accommodation.

label: house
gloss: A dwelling unit inhabited by a single household (a family or small group sharing facilities such as a kitchen). Houses forming half of a semi-detached pair, or one of a row of terraced houses, should share at least two nodes with joined neighbours, thereby defining the party wall between the properties.

label: houseboat
gloss: A boat used primarily as a home

label: residential
gloss: A general tag for a building used primarily for residential purposes. Where additional detail is available consider using 'apartments', 'terrace', 'house', 'detached' or 'semidetached house'.

label: semidetached house
gloss: A residential house that shares a common wall with another on one side. Typically called a "duplex" in American English.

label: static caravan
gloss: A mobile home (semi)permanently left on a single site

label: terrace
gloss: A single way used to define the outline of a linear row of residential dwellings, each of which normally has its own entrance, which form a terrace ("row-house" or "townhouse" in North American English). Consider defining each dwelling separately using 'house'.

label: commercial
gloss: A building for non-specific commercial activities, not necessarily an office building.

label: industrial
gloss: A building for industrial purposes. Use warehouse if the purpose is known to be primarily for storage/distribution.

label: kiosk
gloss: A small one-room retail building.

label: office
gloss: An office building.

label: retail
gloss: A building primarily used for selling goods that are sold to the public.

label: supermarket
gloss: A building constructed to house a self-service large-area store.

label: warehouse
gloss: A building primarily intended for the storage or goods or as part of a distribution system.

label: cathedral
gloss: A building that was built as a cathedral.

label: chapel
gloss: A building that was built as a chapel.

label: church
gloss: A building that was built as a church.

label: monastery
gloss: A building constructed as monastery. Often, monasteries are consisting of several distinct buildings with specific functions.

label: mosque
gloss: A building errected as mosque.

label: presbytery
gloss: A building where priests live and work.

label: religious
gloss: Unspecific building related to religion. Prefer more specific values if possible.

label: shrine
gloss: A building that was built as a shrine.

label: synagogue
gloss: A building that was built as a synagogue.

label: temple
gloss: A building that was built as a temple.

label: bakehouse
gloss: A building that was built as a bakehouse (i.e. for baking bread).

label: civic
gloss: A generic tag for a building created to house some civic amenity.

label: fire station
gloss: A building constructed as fire station, i.e. to house fire fighting equipment and officers, regardless of current use.

label: government
gloss: For government buildings in general, including municipal, provincial and divisional secretaries, government agencies and departments, town halls, (regional) parliaments and court houses.

label: hospital
gloss: A building errected for a hospital.

label: public
gloss: A building constructed as accessible to the general public (a town hall, police station, court house, etc.).

label: toilets
gloss: A toilet block.

label: train station
gloss: A building constructed to be a train station building, including buildings that are abandoned and used nowadays for a different purpose.

label: transportation
gloss: A building related to public transport.

label: kindergarten
gloss: For any generic kindergarten buildings. Buildings for specific uses (sports halls etc.) should be tagged for their purpose.

label: school
gloss: A building errected as school. Buildings for specific uses (sports halls etc.) should be tagged for their purpose.

label: university
gloss: A university building.

label: university college
gloss: A university building.

label: university college
gloss: A college building.

label: college
gloss: A college building.

label: barn
gloss: An agricultural building used for storage and as a covered workplace.

label: conservatory
gloss: A building or room having glass or tarpaulin roofing and walls used as an indoor garden or a sunroom (winter garden).

label: cowshed
gloss: A cowshed (cow barn, cow house) is a building for housing cows, usually found on farms.

label: farm auxiliary
gloss: A building on a farm that is not a dwelling (use 'farm' or 'house' for the farm house).

label: greenhouse
gloss: A greenhouse is a glass or plastic covered building used to grow plants.

label: slurry tank
gloss: A circular building built to hold a liquid mix of primarily animal excreta (also known as slurry).

label: stable
gloss: A stable is a building where horses are kept.

label: sty
gloss: A sty (pigsty, pig ark, pig-shed) is a building for raising domestic pigs, usually found on farms.

label: grandstand
gloss: The main stand, usually roofed, commanding the best view for spectators at racecourses or sports grounds.

label: pavilion
gloss: A sports pavilion usually with changing rooms, storage areas and possibly an space for functions & events. Avoid using this term for other structures called pavilions by architects (see [W] Pavilion)

label: riding hall
gloss: A building that was built as a riding hall.

label: sports hall
gloss: A building that was built as a sports hall.

label: stadium
gloss: A building constructed to be a stadium building, including buildings that are abandoned and used nowadays for a different purpose.

label: hangar
gloss: A hangar is a building used for the storage of airplanes, helicopters or space-craft.

label: hut
gloss: A hut is a small and crude shelter. Note that this word has two meanings.

label: shed
gloss: A shed is a simple, single-storey structure in a back garden or on an allotment that is used for storage, hobbies, or as a workshop.

label: carport
gloss: A carport is a covered structure used to offer limited protection to vehicles, primarily cars, from the elements. Unlike most structures a carport does not have four walls, and usually has one or two.

label: garage
gloss: A garage is a building suitable for the storage of one or possibly more motor vehicle or similar.

label: garages
gloss: A building that consists of a number of discrete storage spaces for different owners/tenants.

label: parking
gloss: Structure purpose-built for parking cars.

label: car park
gloss: Structure purpose-built for parking cars.

label: digester
gloss: A digester is a bioreactor for the production of inflatable biogas from biomass.

label: service
gloss: Service building usually is a small unmanned building with certain machinery (like pumps or transformers).

label: transformer tower
gloss: A transformer tower is a characteristic tall building comprising a distribution transformer and constructed to connect directly to a medium voltage overhead power line.

label: water tower
gloss: A water tower

label: military
gloss: A military building.

label: bunker
gloss: A hardened military building.

label: bridge
gloss: A building used as a bridge.

label: construction
gloss: Used for buildings under construction.

label: container
gloss: For a container used as a permanent building. Do not map containers placed temporarily, for example used in shipping or contraction.

label: marquee
gloss: For a tent or easily demountable tent-like building.

label: gatehouse
gloss: An entry control point building, spanning over a highway that enters a city or compound.

label: roof
gloss: A structure that consists of a roof with open sides, such as a rain shelter, and also gas stations

label: ruins
gloss: Frequently used for a house or other building that is abandoned and in poor repair. However, some believe this usage is incorrect, and the tag should only be used for buildings constructed as fake ruins (for example sham ruins in an English landscape garden). See also lifecycle tagging.

label: alpine hut
gloss: Alpine hut or a mountain hut is a remote building positioned in the mountains designed to provided lodging accommodation for mountaineers, climbers and hikers. The access is usually restricted to foot, mountain bike or ski. Typically, these are operated by an Alpine Club or a similar organisation.

label: apartment
gloss: A holiday or vacation apartment is a furnished apartment or flat with cooking and bathroom facilities that can be rented for holiday vacations. This tag can be applied to a building accommodating one or more holiday flats.

label: aquarium
gloss: An aquarium, meant as Public aquarium is the aquatic counterpart of a zoo with living aquatic animals for public viewing.

label: artwork
gloss: Artwork is used to tag public pieces of art. Typically, these are outdoors.

label: attraction
gloss: Attraction or tourist attraction is a general place of interest for visitors. Typically used for its natural or historical significance.

label: camp pitch
gloss: camp pitch is the free space used to place a tent or or caravan within a camp site or caravan site area.

label: caravan site
gloss: Caravan site, caravan park or RV park is an area where people with caravans, motorhomes, recreational vehicles can stay overnight, or longer, in allotted spaces known as "pitches" or "sites". They usually provide facilities including toilets, waste disposal, water supply, power supply etc.

label: chalet
gloss: Chalet is a type of accommodation used in the hospitality industry to describe one or more detached cottages with self-contained cooking facilities and/or bathroom and toilet facilities.

label: gallery
gloss: Art gallery or art museum is an area or typically a building that displays a variety of visual art exhibitions; The most common exhibits being paintings, sculpture or photography.

label: guest house
gloss: Guest houses, similar to a Hostel, provides lodging accommodation without a hotel license that is typically owner-operated. They usually offer a private room served with breakfast, but the staff is not convenient around-the-clock. These range from custom-built guest houses to family-based homes, frequently refer to as a bed and breakfast.

label: hostel
gloss: Hostels provide inexpensive accommodation, typically with them having shared bedrooms, bathrooms, kitchens, and lounges.

label: hotel
gloss: Hotels provide accommodation for guests with usually numbered rooms. Some facilities provided may include a basic bed, storage for clothing and additional guest facilities may include swimming pool, childcare, and conference facilities.

label: information
gloss: Information, visitor center or centre, visitor information center or tourist information center is an information source for tourists, travellers and visitors.

label: motel
gloss: Motel is an abbreviation which is shortened by the term "motor hotel". It's an establishment that provides accommodation designed for motorists usually on a short-term basis, with convenient parking for motor cars at or close to the room.

label: museum
gloss: Museum is an institution which has exhibitions on scientific, historical, artistic, or cultural artifacts. Typically these are open to the public as a tourist attraction.

label: picnic site
gloss: Picnic site is an area that is suitable for eating outdoors and may have a number of facilities within it. For example they might include: toilets, water taps for drinking or cleaning, BBQ grills, benches, table with benches (picnic tables) and covered structures for bad weather. They also may be used on a grassy area that is popular for picnics.

label: theme park
gloss: Theme park or amusement park is an area where entertainment is provided by rides, game concessions, etc., catering to large numbers to people. For example: Disneyland, Magic Kingdom, Universal Studios Florida, Europa Park, and Ocean Park.

label: viewpoint
gloss: Viewpoint, also known as a overlook, observation point, lookout, viewing point, scenic area or vista point is a place for visitors, often high, with good a scenery view of the surrounding countryside or notable buildings.

label: wilderness hut
gloss: Wilderness hut or backcountry hut is a remote building, with generally a fireplace, intended to provide temporary shelter and sleeping accommodation. See also Bothy

label: zoo
gloss: Zoo is an abbreviation for a zoological garden or park that has confined animals on display for viewing by the public.

label: alcohol
gloss: Shop selling alcohol to take away

label: bakery
gloss: Shop focused on selling bread

label: beverages
gloss: Shop focused on selling alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverages.

label: brewing supplies
gloss: Shop focused on selling supplies for home brewing of beer, wine and spirits (where permitted).

label: butcher
gloss: Shop focused on selling meat

label: cheese
gloss: Shop focused on selling cheese.

label: chocolate
gloss: Shop focused on selling chocolate.

label: coffee
gloss: Shop focused on selling coffee.

label: confectionery
gloss: Shop focused on selling sweets or candy

label: convenience
gloss: A small local shop carrying a small subset of the items you would find in a supermarket

label: deli
gloss: Shop focused on selling delicatessen (fine foods, gourmet foods), possibly also fine wine. Not to be confused with the US delis.

label: dairy
gloss: Shop focused on selling dairy products.

label: farm
gloss: Shop or roadside stand focused on selling freshly harvested farm produce

label: frozen food
gloss: Shop focused on selling frozen food.

label: greengrocer
gloss: Shop focused on selling vegetables and fruits.

label: health food
gloss: A health food shop; selling wholefoods, vitamins, nutrition supplements and meat and dairy alternatives.

label: ice cream
gloss: Shop selling ice cream.

label: organic
gloss: Shop focused on selling organic food.

label: pasta
gloss: Shop focused on selling (fresh) pasta, ravioli, etc.

label: pastry
gloss: Shop focused on selling baked sweets like cakes, biscuits, strudel and pies.

label: seafood
gloss: Shop focused on selling fish/seafood.

label: spices
gloss: Shop focused on selling spices.

label: tea
gloss: Shop focused on selling tea.

label: water
gloss: Shop focused on selling drinking water.

label: general
gloss: A store that carries a general line of merchandise.

label: kiosk
gloss: A small shop on the pavement that sells magazines, tobacco, newspapers, sweets and stamps.

label: mall
gloss: A shopping mall – multiple stores under one roof (also known as a shopping centre)

label: supermarket
gloss: Supermarket – a large store with groceries and other items

label: wholesale
gloss: Wholesale/warehouse club or cash and carry - a store that sells items in bulk to retailers.

label: bag
gloss: Shop focused on selling bags.

label: boutique
gloss: A small shopping outlet, especially one that specializes in elite and fashionable items

label: clothes
gloss: Shop focused on selling clothes and/or underwear (other related value in use is fashion)

label: fabric
gloss: Shop focused on selling fabric and other materials for the purpose of making clothes and other products, eg dress making.

label: jewelry
gloss: Jewellers shops.

label: leather
gloss: Shop focused on selling products made out of leather.

label: sewing
gloss: A shop that sells sewing supplies (fabric, thread, yarn, knitting needles, sewing machines, etc.)

label: shoes
gloss: Shop focused on selling shoes.

label: tailor
gloss: A place where clothing is made, repaired, or altered professionally, especially suits and men's clothing

label: watches
gloss: Shop focused on selling watches.

label: wool
gloss: Shop selling wool for making of clothes or other products.

label: charity
gloss: A charity shop is a shop operated by a charity, for the purposes of fundraising.

label: variety store
gloss: A variety store retailer is a retail store that sells inexpensive items, sometimes with a single price point for all items in the store.

label: beauty
gloss: A non-hairdresser beauty shop, spa, nail salon, etc.

label: chemist
gloss: Shop focused on selling articles of personal hygiene, cosmetics, and household cleaning products.

label: cosmetics
gloss: Shop focused on selling cosmetics

label: erotic
gloss: Shop focused on selling erotic toys, -clothes or other erotic stuff.

label: hairdresser
gloss: Here you can get your hair cut, coloured.

label: hearing aids
gloss: Shop focused on selling hearing aids devices

label: herbalist
gloss: Shop focused on selling herbs, often for medical purposes.

label: massage
gloss: A massage shop

label: medical supply
gloss: Shop focused on selling medical supplies.

label: nutrition supplements
gloss: Shops that sells one or more nutritional supplements (of vitamins, minerals and/or herbs)

label: optician
gloss: Shop focused on selling eyeglasses, contact lenses (may also check your eyes).

label: perfumery
gloss: Shop focused on selling perfumery

label: tattoo
gloss: A tattoo parlour.

label: agrarian
gloss: Shop focused on selling agrarian products, like seeds, agricultural machinery, animal feed, etc.

label: appliance
gloss: Shop focused on selling large electrical items (aka white goods) washing machines, fridges, cookers, ovens, fans, etc.

label: bathroom furnishing
gloss: Shop focused on selling bathroom furniture and accessories

label: doityourself
gloss: Shop focused on selling tools and supplies to do-it-yourself householders, gardening, …

label: electrical
gloss: Shop focused on selling electrical supplies and devices

label: energy
gloss: Shop focused on selling energy

label: fireplace
gloss: Shop focused on selling electric fireplaces, stoves or masonry heaters and required fuels

label: florist
gloss: Shop focused on selling bouquets of flowers.

label: garden furniture
gloss: Shop focused on selling garden furniture (sheds, outdoor tables, gates, fences, ...).

label: gas
gloss: Shop focused on selling technical gas, such as argon, oxygen, acetylene, nitrogen, carbon dioxide, etc. in pressurized containers

label: glaziery
gloss: Shop focused on selling and installing glazing for windows and doors.

label: groundskeeping
gloss: Shop focused on selling outdoor groundskeeping equipment (lawnmowers, chainsaws, small tractors, ...

label: hardware
gloss: Shop focused on selling building supplies including screws, bolts & paints.

label: houseware
gloss: Shop focused on selling crockery, cutlery, kitchenware, small household appliances.

label: locksmith
gloss: Shop focused on selling keys.

label: paint
gloss: Shop focused on selling paints.

label: security
gloss: Shop focused on selling security items like burglar alarms, vaults, locking systems, etc.

label: trade
gloss: Shop focused on selling one or more building supplies such as timber/wood, cement etc.

label: antiques
gloss: Shop focused on selling antiques.

label: bed
gloss: Shop focused on selling mattresses and other bedding products.

label: candles
gloss: Shop focused on selling candles and candle accessories (holders, etc)

label: carpet
gloss: Shop focused on selling carpets

label: curtain
gloss: Shop focused on selling curtains or drapes

label: doors
gloss: Shop focused on selling doors

label: flooring
gloss: Shop focused on selling floorings

label: furniture
gloss: Shop focused on selling furniture, might range from small decorational items to a whole flat interior

label: interior decoration
gloss: Shop focused on selling interior decorations.

label: kitchen
gloss: A shop where you can plan and buy your kitchen. (Sometimes called "kitchen studio" and the like, but plain kitchen is the most frequently used tag so far.)

label: lighting
gloss: A shop selling lighting fixtures and lamps.

label: tiles
gloss: Shop focused on selling tiles.

label: computer
gloss: Shop focused on selling computers, peripherals, software, …

label: electronics
gloss: Shop focused on selling consumer electronics (TV, radio, …). Larger ones may also sell computers, fridges, …

label: hifi
gloss: Shop focused on selling High Fidelity or High End environment to listen music or watch films at home

label: mobile phone
gloss: Shop focused on selling mobile phones and accessories

label: radiotechnics
gloss: Shop focused on selling electronic components, electrical products, radio measuring devices, supplies for radio and electronics.

label: atv
gloss: Shop focused on selling atvs (quads), atv equipment and may rent or repair them

label: bicycle
gloss: Shop focused on selling bicycles, bicycle equipment and may rent or repair them

label: boat
gloss: Shop focused on selling boats, boat equipment and may rent or repair them

label: car
gloss: Car store – a place to buy cars or to get your car repaired

label: car repair
gloss: Shop focused on car repair (usually independent of a specific car brand).

label: caravan
gloss: A shop for caravans, motorhomes & similar recreational vehicles.

label: fuel
gloss: A massage shop

label: fishing
gloss: Shop focused on selling medical supplies.

label: golf
gloss: Shops that sells one or more nutritional supplements (of vitamins, minerals and/or herbs)

label: hunting
gloss: Shop focused on selling gun and hunting equipment.

label: jetski
gloss: Shop focused on selling jetskis, jetski equipment and may rent or repair them

label: motorcycle
gloss: Shop focused on selling motorcycles and/or related accessories, clothes, parts, and rental services.

label: outdoor
gloss: Shop focused on selling camping, walking, climbing, and other outdoor sports equipment (GPSes, etc.)

label: ski
gloss: Shop focused on selling skis, ski equipment and may rent or repair them

label: sports
gloss: Shop focused on selling sporting goods.

label: swimming pool
gloss: A store that sells swimming pool equipment and supplies.

label: trailer
gloss: Shop focused on selling trailers and parts and/or repairing / renting them

label: tyres
gloss: Shop focused on selling tyres.

label: art
gloss: Shop which sells works of art. May be paintings, sculpture, or other types of art

label: collector
gloss: A shop for different collector's items like stamps, coins, action figures, etc.

label: craft
gloss: An arts and crafts supply store. Commonly sold items are paper, canvas, paint, pencils, crafting wood, crafting tools, etc.

label: frame
gloss: Shop focused on selling frames.

label: games
gloss: Shop focused on selling board games, card games and/or role-playing games.

label: model
gloss: Shop specialising in the sale of scale models.

label: music
gloss: Shop focused on selling recorded music (vinyl/CDs/...)

label: photo
gloss: Shop focused on selling products or services related with photography.

label: camera
gloss: A shop mainly selling cameras and lenses

label: trophy
gloss: Store selling trophies, awards, plaques etc.

label: video
gloss: Shop focused on selling or renting out videos/DVDs.

label: video games
gloss: Shop focused on selling video games.

label: anime
gloss: Shop focused on selling anime stuff.

label: books
gloss: Shop focused on selling books.

label: gift
gloss: Shop focused on selling gifts, greeting cards, or tourist gifts (souvenirs)

label: lottery
gloss: A shop of which the main or only purpose is the sale of lottery tickets.

label: newsagent
gloss: Shop focused on selling newspapers, cigarettes, other goods

label: stationery
gloss: Shop focused on selling office supplies

label: ticket
gloss: Shop focused on selling tickets for concerts, events, public transport, …

label: bookmaker
gloss: A shop that takes bets on sporting and other events at agreed upon odds.

label: cannabis
gloss: a shop primarily and legally selling non-medical cannabis products

label: copyshop
gloss: Shop focused on selling photocopying and printing services.

label: dry cleaning
gloss: Shop or kiosk offering a clothes dry cleaning service. The actual cleaning may be done elsewhere.

label: e-cigarette
gloss: Shop focused on selling electronic cigarettes.

label: laundry
gloss: A shop to get your normal clothes washed. Might be self service coin operated, with service staff for drop off, …

label: money lender
gloss: A money lender offers small personal loans at high rates of interest.

label: party
gloss: A shop for party and festival supplies, like costumes, etc.

label: pawnbroker
gloss: A pawnbroker (or pawnshop) is an individual or business that offers secured loans to people.

label: pet
gloss: A shop for pets, animals and toys or food for them.

label: pet grooming
gloss: A shop offering grooming services for pets (most frequently dogs)

label: pest control
gloss: Shop selling pest control goods to exterminate rats, insects etc.

label: pyrotechnics
gloss: Store of pyrotechnics: fireworks, firecrackers, sparklers etc.

label: religion
gloss: Shop focused on selling religious articles, church shop.

label: storage rental
gloss: self storage

label: tobacco
gloss: Shop focused on selling tobacco, cigarettes and their related accessories.

label: toys
gloss: Shop focused on selling toys.

label: vacant
gloss: Not an actual shop, of course. You may want to use this tag when a shop has been closed, to avoid confusing other mappers who may not know about this. Plus, you can keep the corresponding object and simply edit it when a new shop opens on the same spot.

label: weapons
gloss: Shop focused on selling weapons like knives, guns etc.

label: outpost
gloss: Shop primarily used to pick-up items ordered online.

label: station
gloss: Railway passenger and/or cargo station.

label: tram stop
gloss: A tram stop is a place where a passenger can embark / disembark a tram.

label: historic aircraft
gloss: A decommissioned aircraft which generally remains in one place.

label: historic aqueduct
gloss: A historic structure to convey water

label: historic archaeological site
gloss: A place in which evidence of past activity is preserved.

label: historic battlefield
gloss: The site of a battle or military skirmish in the past.

label: historic boundary stone
gloss: A historic physical marker that identifies a boundary

label: historic building
gloss: Unspecified historic building.

label: historic cannon
gloss: A historic/retired cannon. Usually found on forts or battlefields.

label: historic castle
gloss: Used for various kinds of castles, palaces, fortresses, manors, stately homes, kremlins, shiros and other.

label: historic castle wall
gloss: A fortification surrounding the bailey of a castle

label: historic church
gloss: A church with a historical value.

label: historic citywalls
gloss: A citywall is a fortification used to defend a city.

label: historic farm
gloss: A historical farm, kept in its original state.

label: historic fort
gloss: A military fort, a stand-alone defensive structure which differs from a castle in that there is no permanent residence

label: historic gallows
gloss: remains of a gallows

label: historic locomotive
gloss: A decommissioned locomotive which generally remains in one place

label: historic manor
gloss: Historic manors/mansions having different use today

label: historic memorial
gloss: Small memorials, usually remembering special persons, people who lost their lives in the wars, past events or missing places.

label: historic milestone
gloss: A historic marker that shows the distance to important destinations

label: historic monastery
gloss: Building/place that is a historically significant monastery.

label: historic monument
gloss: A memorial object, which is especially large, built to remember, show respect to a person or group of people or to commemorate an event.

label: historic pillory
gloss: A pillory.

label: historic ruins
gloss: Remains of structures that were once complete, but have fallen into partial or complete disrepair.

label: historic ship
gloss: A decommissioned ship/submarine which generally remains in one place

label: historic tank
gloss: A decommissioned tank which generally remains in one place

label: historic tomb
gloss: A structure where somebody has been buried.

label: historic tower
gloss: This property distinguishes a tower as historic

label: historic wayside cross
gloss: A historical cross, symbol of christian faith.

label: historic wayside shrine
gloss: A shrine often showing a religious depiction. Tag is used also for modern shrines.

label: historic wreck
gloss: A nautical craft that has been sunk or destroyed.

label: bar
gloss: Bar is a purpose-built commercial establishment that sells alcoholic drinks to be consumed on the premises. They are characterised by a noisy and vibrant atmosphere, similar to a party and usually don't sell food.

label: biergarten
gloss: Biergarten or beer garden is an open-air area where alcoholic beverages along with food is prepared and served. See also the description of the tags amenity=pub;bar;restaurant. A biergarten can commonly be found attached to a beer hall, pub, bar, or restaurant.

label: cafe
gloss: Cafe is generally an informal place that offers casual meals and beverages; typically, the focus is on coffee or tea. Also known as a coffeehouse/shop, bistro or sidewalk cafe.

label: fast food
gloss: Fast food restaurant. The kind of food served can be tagged with cuisines and diets.

label: food court
gloss: An area with several different restaurant food counters and a shared eating area. Commonly found in malls, airports, etc.

label: ice cream
gloss: Ice cream shop or ice cream parlour. A place that sells ice cream and frozen yoghurt over the counter

label: pub
gloss: A place selling beer and other alcoholic drinks; may also provide food or accommodation (UK).

label: restaurant
gloss: Restaurant (not fast food). The kind of food served can be tagged with cuisines and diets.

label: college
gloss: Campus or buildings of an institute of Further Education (aka continuing education)

label: driving school
gloss: Driving School which offers motor vehicle driving lessons

label: kindergarten
gloss: For children too young for a regular school (also known as preschool, playschool or nursery school), in some countries including afternoon supervision of primary school children.

label: language school
gloss: Language School is an educational institution where one studies a foreign language.

label: library
gloss: A public library (municipal, university, …) to borrow books from.

label: toy library
gloss: A place to borrow games and toys, or play with them on site.

label: music school
gloss: A music school, an educational institution specialized in the study, training, and research of music.

label: school
gloss: School and grounds - primary, middle and seconday schools.

label: university
gloss: An university campus: an institute of higher education

label: bicycle parking
gloss: Parking for bicycles.

label: bicycle repair station
gloss: General tools for self-service bicycle repairs, usually on the roadside; no service

label: bicycle rental
gloss: Rent a bicycle

label: boat rental
gloss: Rent a Boat

label: boat sharing
gloss: Share a Boat

label: bus station
gloss: May also be tagged as public_transport station.

label: car rental
gloss: Rent a car

label: car sharing
gloss: Share a car

label: car wash
gloss: Wash a car

label: vehicle inspection
gloss: Government vehicle inspection

label: charging station
gloss: Charging facility for electric vehicles

label: ferry terminal
gloss: Ferry terminal/stop. A place where people/cars/etc. can board and leave a ferry.

label: gas station
gloss: Petrol station; gas station; marine fuel; … Streets to petrol stations are often tagged highway service.

label: fuel
gloss: Petrol station; gas station; marine fuel; … Streets to petrol stations are often tagged highway service.

label: grit bin
gloss: A container that holds grit or a mixture of salt and grit.

label: motorcycle parking
gloss: Parking for motorcycles

label: parking
gloss: Car park. Nodes and areas (without access tag) will get a parking symbol. Areas will be coloured. Streets on car parking are often tagged highway=service and service=parking_aisle.

label: parking entrance
gloss: An entrance or exit to an underground or multi-storey parking facility. Group multiple parking entrances together with a relation using the tags type=site and site=parking. Do not mix with amenity=parking.

label: parking space
gloss: A single parking space. Group multiple parking spaces together with a relation using the tags type=site and site=parking. Do not mix with amenity=parking.

label: taxi
gloss: A place where taxis wait for passengers.

label: atm
gloss: ATM or cash point: a device that provides the clients of a financial institution with access to financial transactions.

label: bank
gloss: Bank or credit union: a financial establishment where customers can deposit and withdraw money, take loans, make investments and transfer funds.

label: bureau de change
gloss: Bureau de change, money changer, currency exchange, Wechsel, cambio – a place to change foreign bank notes and travellers cheques.

label: baby hatch
gloss: A place where a baby can be, out of necessity, anonymously left to be safely cared for and perhaps adopted.

label: clinic
gloss: A medium-sized medical facility or health centre.

label: dentist
gloss: A dentist practice / surgery.

label: doctors
gloss: A doctor's practice / surgery.

label: hospital
gloss: A hospital providing in-patient medical treatment. Often used in conjunction with emergency=* to note whether the medical centre has emergency facilities.

label: nursing home
gloss: Discouraged tag for a home for disabled or elderly persons who need permanent care. Use amenity=social_facility + social_facility=nursing_home now.

label: pharmacy
gloss: Pharmacy: a shop where a pharmacist sells medications dispensing=yes/no - availability of prescription-only medications

label: social facility
gloss: A facility that provides social services: group & nursing homes, workshops for the disabled, homeless shelters, etc.

label: veterinary
gloss: A place where a veterinary surgeon, also known as a veterinarian or vet, practices.

label: arts centre
gloss: A venue where a variety of arts are performed or conducted

label: brothel
gloss: An establishment specifically dedicated to prostitution

label: casino
gloss: A gambling venue with at least one table game(e.g. roulette, blackjack) that takes bets on sporting and other events at agreed upon odds.

label: cinema
gloss: A place where films are shown (US: movie theater)

label: community centre
gloss: A place mostly used for local events, festivities and group activities; including special interest and special age groups.

label: conference centre
gloss: A large building that is used to hold a convention

label: events venue
gloss: A building specifically used for organising events

label: fountain
gloss: A fountain for cultural / decorational / recreational purposes.

label: gambling
gloss: A place for gambling, not being a shop=bookmaker, shop=lottery, amenity=casino, or leisure=adult_gaming_centre.

label: nightclub
gloss: A place to drink and dance (nightclub). The German word is "Disco" or "Discothek". Please don't confuse this with the German "Nachtclub" which is most likely amenity=stripclub.

label: planetarium
gloss: A planetarium.

label: public bookcase
gloss: A street furniture containing books. Take one or leave one.

label: social centre
gloss: A place for free and not-for-profit activities.

label: stripclub
gloss: A place that offers striptease or lapdancing (for sexual services use amenity=brothel).

label: studio
gloss: TV radio or recording studio

label: swingerclub
gloss: A club where people meet to have a party and group sex.

label: theatre
gloss: A theatre or opera house where live performances occur, such as plays, musicals and formal concerts. Use amenity=cinema for movie theaters.

label: courthouse
gloss: A building home to a court of law, where justice is dispensed

label: embassy
gloss: An embassy, consulate or diplomatic office. Also see office=diplomatic

label: fire station
gloss: A station of a fire brigade

label: police
gloss: A police station where police officers patrol from and that is a first point of contact for civilians

label: post box
gloss: A box for the reception of mail. Alternative mail-carriers can be tagged via operator=*

label: post depot
gloss: Post depot or delivery office, where letters and parcels are collected and sorted prior to delivery.

label: post office
gloss: Post office building with postal services

label: prison
gloss: A prison or jail where people are incarcerated before trial or after conviction

label: ranger station
gloss: National Park visitor headquarters: official park visitor facility with police, visitor information, permit services, etc

label: townhall
gloss: Building where the administration of a village, town or city may be located, or just a community meeting place

label: bbq
gloss: BBQ or Barbecue is a permanently built grill for cooking food, which is most typically used outdoors by the public. For example these may be found in city parks or at beaches. Use the tag fuel=* to specify the source of heating, such as fuel=wood;electric;charcoal. For mapping nearby table and chairs, see also the tag tourism=picnic_site. For mapping campfires and firepits, instead use the tag leisure=firepit.

label: bench
gloss: A bench to sit down and relax a bit

label: dog toilet
gloss: Area designated for dogs to urinate and excrete.

label: drinking water
gloss: Drinking water is a place where humans can obtain potable water for consumption. Typically, the water is used for only drinking. Also known as a drinking fountain or bubbler.

label: give box
gloss: A small facility where people drop off and pick up various types of items in the sense of free sharing and reuse.

label: shelter
gloss: A small shelter against bad weather conditions. To additionally describe the kind of shelter use shelter_type=*.

label: shower
gloss: Public shower or bath.

label: telephone
gloss: Public telephone

label: toilets
gloss: Public toilets (might require a fee)

label: water point
gloss: Place where you can get large amounts of drinking water

label: watering place
gloss: Place where water is contained and animals can drink

label: sanitary dump station
gloss: A place for depositing human waste from a toilet holding tank.

label: recycling
gloss: Recycling facilities (bottle banks, etc.). Combine with recycling_type=container for containers or recycling_type=centre for recycling centres.

label: waste basket
gloss: A single small container for depositing garbage that is easily accessible for pedestrians.

label: waste disposal
gloss: A medium or large disposal bin, typically for bagged up household or industrial waste.

label: waste transfer station
gloss: A waste transfer station is a location that accepts, consolidates and transfers waste in bulk.

label: animal boarding
gloss: A facility where you, paying a fee, can bring your animal for a limited period of time (e.g. for holidays)

label: animal breeding
gloss: A facility where animals are bred, usually to sell them

label: animal shelter
gloss: A shelter that recovers animals in trouble

label: baking oven
gloss: An oven used for baking bread and similar, for example inside a building=bakehouse.

label: childcare
gloss: A place where children of different ages are looked after which is not an amenity=kindergarten or preschool.

label: clock
gloss: A public visible clock

label: crematorium
gloss: A place where dead human bodies are burnt

label: dive centre
gloss: A dive center is the base location where sports divers usually start scuba diving or make dive guided trips at new locations.

label: funeral hall
gloss: A place for holding a funeral ceremony, other than a place of worship.

label: grave yard
gloss: A (smaller) place of burial, often you'll find a church nearby. Large places should be landuse=cemetery instead.

label: gym
gloss: Deprecated. Use leisure=fitness_centre or leisure=sports_centre instead. A place which houses exercise equipment for the purpose of physical exercise.

label: hunting stand
gloss: A hunting stand: an open or enclosed platform used by hunters to place themselves at an elevated height above the terrain

label: internet cafe
gloss: A place whose principal role is providing internet services to the public.

label: kitchen
gloss: A public kitchen in a facility to use by everyone or customers

label: lounger
gloss: An object for people to lie down.

label: marketplace
gloss: A marketplace where goods and services are traded daily or weekly.

label: monastery
gloss: Monastery is the location of a monastery or a building in which monks and nuns live.

label: photo booth
gloss: Photo Booth – A stand to create instant photo.

label: place of worship
gloss: A church, mosque, or temple, etc. Note that you also need religion=*, usually denomination=* and preferably name=* as well as amenity=place_of_worship.

label: public bath
gloss: A location where the public may bathe in common, etc. japanese onsen, turkish bath, hot spring

label: public building
gloss: A generic public building. Don't use! See office=government.

label: vending machine
gloss: A machine selling goods – food, tickets, newspapers, etc. Add type of goods using vending=*

label: wood
gloss: Tree-covered area (a 'forest' or 'wood'). Also see landuse=forest. For more detail, one can use leaf_type=* and leaf_cycle=*.

label: tree row
gloss: A line of trees.

label: tree
gloss: A single tree.

label: scrub
gloss: Uncultivated land covered with shrubs, bushes or stunted trees.

label: heath
gloss: A dwarf-shrub habitat, characterised by open, low growing woody vegetation, often dominated by plants of the Ericaceae.

label: moor
gloss: Don't use, see wikipage. Upland areas, characterised by low-growing vegetation on acidic soils.

label: grassland
gloss: Areas where the vegetation is dominated by grasses (Poaceae) and other herbaceous (non-woody) plants. For mown/managed grass see landuse=grass, for hay/pasture see landuse=meadow.

label: fell
gloss: Habitat above the tree line covered with grass, dwarf shrubs and mosses.

label: tundra
gloss: Habitat above tree line in alpine and subpolar regions, principally covered with uncultivated grass, low growing shrubs and mosses and sometimes grazed.

label: bare rock
gloss: An area with sparse or no vegetation, so that the bedrock becomes visible.

label: scree
gloss: Unconsolidated angular rocks formed by rockfall and weathering from adjacent rockfaces.

label: shingle
gloss: An accumulation of rounded rock fragments on a beach or riverbed

label: sand
gloss: An area covered by sand with no or very little vegetation. See natural=beach and natural=dune as well.

label: mud
gloss: Area covered with mud: water saturated fine grained soil without significant plant growth. Also see natural=wetland + wetland=* if the surfaces are unknown.

label: water
gloss: Any body of water, from natural such as a lake or pond to artificial like moat or canal. Also see waterway=riverbank

label: wetland
gloss: A natural area subject to inundation or with waterlogged ground, further specified with wetland=*

label: bay
gloss: An area of water mostly surrounded by land but with a level connection to the ocean or a lake.

label: cape
gloss: A piece of elevated land sticking out into the sea or large lake. Includes capes, heads, headlands and (water) promontories.

label: strait
gloss: A narrow area of water surrounded by land on two sides and by water on two other sides.

label: beach
gloss: landform along a body of water which consists of sand, shingle or other loose material

label: coastline
gloss: The mean high water springs line between the sea and land (with the water on the right side of the way.)

label: reef
gloss: A feature (rock, sandbar, coral, etc) lying beneath the surface of the water

label: spring
gloss: A place where ground water flows naturally from the ground (Other languages).

label: peak
gloss: The top (summit) of a hill or mountain.

label: dune
gloss: A hill of sand formed by wind, covered with no or very little vegetation. See also natural=sand and natural=beach.

label: hill
gloss: A hill.

label: valley
gloss: node A natural depression flanked by ridges or ranges of mountains or hills

label: ridge
gloss: A mountain or hill linear landform with a continuous elevated crest

label: arete
gloss: An arête, a thin, almost knife-like, ridge of rock which is typically formed when two glaciers erode parallel U-shaped valleys.

label: cliff
gloss: A vertical or almost vertical natural drop in terrain, usually with a bare rock surface (leave the lower face to the right of the way).

label: saddle
gloss: The lowest point along a ridge or between two mountain tops

label: peninsula
gloss: A piece of land projecting into water from a larger land mass, nearly surrounded by water

label: rock
gloss: A notable rock or group of rocks attached to the underlying bedrock.

label: stone
gloss: A single notable freestanding rock, which may differ from the composition of the terrain it lies in.; e.g., glacial erratic.

label: sinkhole
gloss: A natural depression or hole in the surface topography.

label: cave entrance
gloss: The entrance to a cave: a natural underground space large enough for a human to enter.

label: river
gloss: A river is a wide, natural watercourse that flows from a source to an ocean, sea, lake or another river. For narrow naturally-formed waterways, see waterway=stream.

label: riverbank
gloss: Sometimes used for larger rivers in addition to waterway=river, to define an area between the opposite riverbanks. Also see water=river with natural=water.

label: stream
gloss: A naturally-formed waterway that is too narrow to be classed as a river. An active, able-bodied person should be able to jump over it.

label: tidal channel
gloss: A natural tidal waterway within the coastal marine environment with bi-directional flow of salty water which depends on the tides.

label: canal
gloss: An artificial open flow waterway used to carry useful water for transportation, waterpower, or irrigation. (Other languages).

label: pressurised
gloss: A waterway where water is flowing in a fully enclosed conduit and subject to pressure; this includes gravity-driven penstocks and siphons and pump-driven pipelines, for example.

label: drain
gloss: An artificial free flow waterway used for carrying superfluous water like storm water or industrial discharge, usually lined with concrete, stones or similar.

label: ditch
gloss: An small artificial free flow waterway used for carrying superfluous water for drainage purposes, usually unlined.

label: fairway
gloss: A navigable route in a lake or sea marked by buoys. The navigable area marked by the buoys can be mapped with seamark:type=fairway.

label: fish pass
gloss: A  fish pass, also known as a fish ladder, a fishway or fish steps, is a structure on or around artificial barriers (such as dams and locks) to facilitate diadromous fishes natural migration.

label: dock
gloss: An 'enclosed' area of water used for building or repairing ships.

label: boatyard
gloss: Boat yard – a place for constructing, repairing and storing vessels out of the water.

label: dam
gloss: A wall built across a river or stream to impound the water. A dam normally does not have water flowing over the top of it.

label: weir
gloss: A barrier built across a river to control speed and depth. Water can still flow over the top.

label: waterfall
gloss: A waterfall, use in combination with natural=cliff

label: rapids
gloss: A natural barrier, formed by a fast-flowing, often turbulent, section of the watercourse.

label: lock gate
gloss: To mark the position of gates at each end of a lock. Alternatively, for smaller locks use a single lock=yes node in the middle of the lock.

label: river
gloss: The water area of a river. Should contain waterway=river way inside.

label: lake
gloss: A lake: a body of relatively still fresh or salt water, localized in a basin that is surrounded by land. Artificially created lakes should instead be tagged as water=pond or water=reservoir. Intermittent lakes (which disappear seasonally) should be tagged with intermittent=yes; salt lakes — with salt=yes.

label: stream
gloss: The water covered area of a stream: a naturally-formed watercourse which is narrower than a river

label: oxbow
gloss: An oxbow lake: U-shaped body of water formed when a wide meander from the main stem of a river is cut off to create a lake.

label: lagoon
gloss: A lagoon: a body of shallow sea water or brackish water separated from the sea by some form of barrier. It's better to specify saltness of water with salt=yes/no.

label: stream pool
gloss: A stream pool; a small and usually deep collection of fresh water, occurring along a stream. Water velocity in the pool is typically much lower than in the stream. Frequently found below a waterfall. May be used as a "swimming hole".

label: reservoir
gloss: A reservoir or an artificial lake is used to store water. Usually formed by a dam over a natural water course, water then backs up into a natural valley or depression. Also see landuse=reservoir

label: basin
gloss: An area of land artificially graded to hold water. For more details you can use basin=*. Also see the much more common tag landuse=basin

label: commercial
gloss: Predominantly commercial businesses and their offices. Commercial businesses which sell goods should be categorised as landuse=retail. Commercial businesses can sell services on site and may include private Doctor's Surgeries, and those non-government services for mental and physical health, such as a Counsellor's or Physiotherapist's practice or Veterinary. Government services and businesses should not use this tag. Commercial businesses can also include office buildings and business parks which have limited interface with the public and sell their services either on site, or externally. Commercial businesses have low amounts of public foot traffic.

label: education
gloss: An area predominately used for educational purposes/facilities.

label: industrial
gloss: Predominantly industrial landuses such as workshops, factories, or warehouses.

label: residential
gloss: Land where people reside; predominantly residential detached (single houses, grouped dwellings), or attached (apartments, flats, units) dwellings. For "Mixed-Use" areas where more than half of the land is residential, tag as residential.

label: retail
gloss: Predominantly retail businesses such as shops. Retail businesses sell physical goods such as food (prepared or grocery), clothing, medicine, stationary, appliances, tools, or other similar physical items. Retail businesses have high amounts of public foot traffic. Retail businesses do not exclusively provide or sell their services. For businesses which sell services see landuse=commercial.

label: allotments
gloss: A piece of land given over to local residents for growing vegetables and flowers.

label: farmland
gloss: An area of farmland used for tillage (cereals, vegetables, oil plants, flowers).

label: farmyard
gloss: An area of land with farm buildings like farmhouse, dwellings, farmsteads, sheds, stables, barns, equipment sheds, feed bunkers, etc. plus the open space in between them and the shrubbery/trees around them.

label: flowerbed
gloss: An area designated for flowers

label: forest
gloss: Managed forest or woodland plantation (Other languages). Some use this to map an area of trees rather than the use of the land. See Forest.

label: meadow
gloss: A meadow or pasture: land primarily vegetated by grass and non-woody plants, mainly used for hay or grazing

label: orchard
gloss: intentional planting of trees or shrubs maintained for food production

label: vineyard
gloss: A piece of land where grapes are grown.

label: basin
gloss: An area artificially graded to hold water.

label: brownfield
gloss: Describes land scheduled for new development where old buildings have been demolished and cleared

label: cemetery
gloss: Place for burials. You can add religion=* (values listed in the place of worship page). Smaller places (e.g. with a church nearby) may use amenity=grave_yard instead.

label: conservation
gloss: Protected areas (deprecated) Alternate tagging of same thing: boundary=protected_area, protected_area=*

label: depot
gloss: An area used as a depot for e.g. vehicles (trains, buses or trams). Consider using rather standard landuse tags like landuse=railway, landuse=commercial, landuse=industrial, with subtag like industrial=depot.

label: garages
gloss: One level buildings with boxes commonly for cars, usually made of brick and metal. Usually this area belong to garage cooperative with own name, chairman, budget, rules, security, etc.

label: grass
gloss: An area of mown and managed grass. Some view this as not a landuse, see the main page landuse=grass for information.

label: greenfield
gloss: Describes land scheduled for new development where there have been no buildings before. A greenfield is scheduled to turn into a construction site

label: greenhouse horticulture
gloss: Area used for growing plants in greenhouses

label: landfill
gloss: Place where waste is dumped.

label: military
gloss: For land areas owned/used by the military for whatever purpose

label: plant nursery
gloss: intentional planting of plants maintaining for the production of new plants

label: port
gloss: coastal industrial area where commercial traffic is handled. Consider using landuse=industrial + industrial=port for this type of industrial area.

label: quarry
gloss: Surface mineral extraction

label: recreation ground
gloss: An open green space for general recreation, which may include pitches, nets and so on, usually municipal but possibly also private to colleges or companies

label: religious
gloss: An area used for religious purposes

label: reservoir
gloss: A Reservoir on Wikipedia. Less popular variant of natural=water + water=reservoir. See also the approved water details proposal and pointers to discussion on talk page.

label: village green
gloss: An area of common land, usually grass, in the centre of a village (quintessentially English – defined separately from 'common land' under the Commons Registration Act 1965 and the Commons Act 2006).

label: winter sports
gloss: An area dedicated to winter sports (e.g. skiing)

label: road
gloss: A road, way, street, motorway etc. It can stand for anything ranging from a footpath to a motorway. This tag should only be used temporarily until the road/way/etc.

label: primary road
gloss: The next most important roads in a country's system. (Often link larger towns.)

label: secondary road
gloss: The next most important roads in a country's system. (Often link towns.)

label: tertiary road
gloss: The next most important roads in a country's system. (Often link smaller towns and villages)

label: bus way
gloss: A dedicated roadway for bus rapid transit systems

label: aerodrome
gloss: Aerodrome in the United Kingdom or Airport in North America is used to map the main area details (other than helicopters only).

label: airport
gloss: Aerodrome in the United Kingdom or Airport in North America is used to map the main area details (other than helicopters only).

label: airport terminal
gloss: Airport terminal is a building at an airport where passengers transfer between ground transportation and the facilities that allow them to board and disembark from aircraft.
